          The brief description of each section in this document are as follows:



Section 0 Introduction #ln; Introduce the FM General Information.#ln;



Section 1 General #ln; Introduce the aircraft general information.#ln;



Section 2 Limitation #ln; Describes the procedures requiring immediate flight crew action and procedures associated with failure of the systems or component.#ln;



Section 3 Emergency and Abnormal Procedures #ln; Describes the procedures requiring emmediate flight crew action and procedures associated with failure of the systems or component.#ln;



Section 4 Normal Procedures #ln; Describes about the procedures associated with systems that are functioning in their usual manner.#ln;



Section 5 Performance #ln; Describes the aircraft performance information that required by the applicable regulation.#ln;



Section 5 Weight and Balance #ln; Describes the instruction applicable to weight and balance control of the aircraft.#ln;

Changes in this book shall be identified as follow:



Markings#ln;

Addition or any changes in this content of book to existing data will be identified by vertical line, located outside margin of applicable page.#ln;

The vertical line will only indicate the current change on each page. Physical relocation of data or the correction of typographical errors, outside of the material revised, will not be identified by a revision bar.#ln;



Issue date#ln;

At the title page, there will be the issue date of this book. At the bottom of each page, there will be the issue date of each data module#ln;



Revision procedure#ln;

To keep this book current, revision will be issued to the lates registered owner of airplane. Revisions to this book consist of:#ln;



List of Effective Data Modules (LEODM)



Change Highlights



Log og Revisions



New or Revised DMs



Temporary Revisions
